<p>On a 4M-token training dataset, OpenAI GPT-4.1 costs $100 to train; Mistral Large 3 costs $16. The training cost difference is dramatic. Inference costs are broadly similar — Mistral is slightly cheaper on output tokens at $9/M vs OpenAI's $12/M. For a high-volume product, the inference delta matters more than the one-time training cost.</p>

<div class="callout">
  <strong>Verify before you rely on these numbers.</strong> Mistral's La Plateforme pricing is published in EUR; the figures above are approximate USD conversions as of April 2026. Check <code>docs.mistral.ai</code> and <code>platform.openai.com/docs</code> for current rates. The DataPrep presets show a <code>lastVerified</code> date when you load them.
</div>

